      "id": "64e2fa86_0d5af770",
      "file_path": "adapters/mso-ve-vnfm-adapter/src/main/java/org/onap/so/adapters/vevnfm/util/NullOptional.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 23,
      "message": "java.util.Optional has ifPresent() method see https://docs.oracle.com/javase/8/docs/api/java/util/Optional.html for more details\n\n\npublic boolean isPresent()\n\nReturn true if there is a value present, otherwise false.\n\nReturns:\n    true if there is a value present, otherwise false",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 3237,
        "name": "Waqas Ikram",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "waqas.ikram@est.tech",
        "username": "waqas.ikram"
      },
      "updated": "2020-04-17 09:59:38.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "66bc7dd6_26426fed",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "id": "2ca1aee4_344d17a8",
      "file_path": "adapters/mso-ve-vnfm-adapter/src/main/java/org/onap/so/adapters/vevnfm/util/NullOptional.java",
      "patchset_number": 2,
      "line": 23,
      "message": "but if this value is null the isPresent() in Optional will return false,\nbut in my NullOptional the isPresent can return TRUE even if value is NULL;\nyou can read it: 'please USE this value (even if it's null)'\nAnd there is NO such functionality within the Optional\nThere are two values within NullOptional: the value itself and a boolean whether we should use the value (the value being null or not doesn't play any role here)\n:-)",
      "author": {
        "account_id": 5336,
        "name": "Piotr Borelowski",
        "display_name": null,
        "email": "p.borelowski@partner.samsung.com",
        "username": "p.borelowski"
      },
      "updated": "2020-04-17 10:29:00.000000000",
      "in_reply_to": "64e2fa86_0d5af770",
      "unresolved": true
    },
